    "methodology": "Base salary drawn from salaries-philippines.json (median monthly USD). Statutory contributions calculated at 2026 rates sourced from SSS, PhilHealth, and Pag-IBIG (all accessed May 2026). SSS employer contribution is 10% of monthly salary credit (MSC), capped at MSC of ₱35,000/month ($568 at May 2026 exchange rate). PhilHealth employer contribution is 2.5% of monthly salary, capped at a salary base of ₱100,000/month ($1,623). Pag-IBIG employer contribution is 2% of monthly salary, capped at a salary base of ₱10,000/month ($162). 13th month pay is a mandatory annual benefit equivalent to one month's basic salary; modeled as 8.33% of monthly base salary (1/12 of annual equivalent). Equipment amortized over 36 months. Management overhead is an industry-typical estimate for organizations using managed remote workforce providers."
